    "functional_description": "Early headlight washer system. J39 relay is energised when: (1) lights are on (E1 terminal 56 powers relay coil), AND (2) washer is activated via E22 terminal 53c. J39 then powers V11 headlight washer pump via heavy 4.0mm² ro (red) wire. V11 pump has 4.0mm² br (brown) earth wire due to high current draw. V5 windscreen washer pump uses lighter 0.5mm² earth. Note that J31 (wash/wipe intermittent relay) position is reserved but may not be fitted on all models.",
    "differences_from_fig_13_80": "Fig 10.35 is the original pre-supplement version. Fig 13.80 (page 289) is the updated version in Chapter 13 Supplement with revised relay designations and connector references. The basic function is identical. Key difference: Fig 10.35 shows J39 with terminals S, 31, P and 4.0mm² pump wiring clearly visible. Fig 13.80 uses the later connector notation (T1a, T1b, T2 etc.)."
  },
